05/10/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Defence Minister Boris Tadic says Serbia-Montenegro is discussing the possibility of sending troops on international missions.
Tadic told reporters on Friday (3 October) that military officials have visited Washington and the US Central Command in Florida for talks on this issue.
He said deployment in Liberia, Afghanistan and Iraq was discussed.
Tadic added that he would consult with all political parties and gauge national consensus on the issue.
The final decision would rest with the Serbia-Montenegro Supreme Defence Council, the Council of Ministers and parliament.
(AP, Tanjug, BBC - 03/10/03)
